Jenkins
===============
create a new ec2-instance and connect in mobaxterm
install git,java and maven
install Jenkins
# wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
# rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
# yum update
# yum install jenkins -y
# systemctl start jenkins
# cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
ff0dfa928b374489a257dde91954d600
open the Jenkins instance in the browser and paste the password
select the select plugins to install => there deselect all the plugins=>click install
asks you to set the password and username =>provide credentials there
in the Jenkins page
go to manage Jenkins (settings) select plugins=>available plugins=>search for git and install git
next maven integration and install it
=>manage jenkins=>tools=>add jdk->name->Java->path to java
=>add git and git path=>(which git)
=>add maven->Maven->path to maven->/opt/tomcat
configure nodes properties
configure new job
use source code management as git
place the git hub url
change branch to */main
place clean install
save and apply and build
